# UC-Pipeline Per-Object Execution Card

**Load this ONCE at session start. Never unload it. Load full phase rules on-demand per step.**

## What this framework is

This pack documents **eToro-derived UC objects downstream of the gold mirrors** — VIEWs in `etoro_kpi*`, MANAGED tables in `de_output` / `bi_output` / `dealing_output`, etc. — that are written by **notebooks or UC stored procedures**.

It is the third SDD pack alongside:

| Pack | Scope | Anchor |
|---|---|---|
| `dwh-semantic-doc/` | Synapse SSDT objects mirrored to UC gold | SSDT `.sql` + Synapse SPs |
| `uc-domain-doc/` | Acquired-company UC (Spaceship, MoneyFarm) | Confluence + Tableau + Genie |
| `uc-pipeline-doc/` (this pack) | eToro-derived UC downstream of gold mirrors | UC `view_definition` + writing notebook (located via `system.access.table_lineage`) |

The pack output goes to `knowledge/UC_generated/{schema}/{Tables|Views}/{Object}.{md|lineage.md|review-needed.md|alter.sql}`.

## Pipeline (standard path)

```
 #     Phase                    Do what                                            Rule file                        Gate    Checkpoint
 0a    Schema Card              Enumerate schema, classify writer, set scope       00-schema-card                   HARD    PHASE 0 CHECKPOINT: PASS
 1     UC Discovery             info_schema columns + DESCRIBE EXTENDED + sample   01-uc-discovery                  HARD    PHASE 1 CHECKPOINT: PASS
 2     Source Code Fetch        view_definition OR writer notebook body            02-source-code-fetch             HARD    PHASE 2 CHECKPOINT: PASS
 3     Upstream Wiki Bridge     Route each upstream UC object to its wiki          03-upstream-wiki-bridge          HARD    PHASE 3 CHECKPOINT: PASS
 4     Column Lineage           Write {Object}.lineage.md from DDL / notebook      04-column-lineage                HARD    PHASE 4 CHECKPOINT: PASS  ← feeds tier assignment
 4.5   Concept Discovery        Mine view DDL / notebook → concepts.json           04.5-concept-discovery           HARD    PHASE 4.5 CHECKPOINT: PASS  ← feeds §2 subsections
 4.6   Formula Extraction       Per-column formula lookup → formulas.json          04.6-formula-extraction          HARD    PHASE 4.6 CHECKPOINT: PASS  ← feeds §4 Tier-2 descriptions
 5     Generate Doc             Write {Object}.md (8 sections) + .review-needed.md 05-generate-doc                  HARD    (shape check)
 6     Deploy                   Generate .alter.sql then apply ALTER COMMENT       06-deploy                        SOFT    (deploy index updated)
```

## Phase Gate Checklist (emit before Phase 5)

```
PHASE GATE CHECK — {Object} ({schema}):
  [x] P0 SchemaCard  [x] P1 Discovery  [x] P2 SourceCode  [x] P3 UpstreamBridge  [x] P4 Lineage
  [x] P4.5 ConceptDiscovery  [x] P4.6 FormulaExtraction
  → Ready for P5
OUTPUT CHECK — {Object}:
  [x] _discovery/source_code/{name}.{sql|py}   [x] _discovery/upstream_wikis/* cached
  [x] {Object}.lineage.md exists   [x] _discovery/concepts/{name}.json exists
  [x] _discovery/formulas/{name}.json exists
  [x] {Object}.md exists (8 sections)   [x] {Object}.review-needed.md exists
  [-] {Object}.alter.sql — deferred to P6
```

**Phase 5 MUST refuse to generate if any `[ ]` (unchecked) box remains.**

## Hard Enforcement Reminders

- **⛔ TARGET SCHEMAS**: The user names the in-scope schemas. Typical set: `etoro_kpi_prep`, `etoro_kpi`, `de_output`, `bi_output`, `dealing_output`, `etoro_kpi_prep_stg`. Do NOT auto-include schemas the user did not name. Bronze ingest schemas (`general`, `trading`, `billing`, `emoney`, `mixpanel`, etc.) and the gold-mirror schemas (`dwh`, `bi_db`, etc.) are NEVER in-scope here — they are documented by `dwh-semantic-doc` or upstream of it.
- **⛔ WRITER FILTER**: Only objects whose writer is a **notebook or UC stored procedure** are in scope. Determine writer via `system.access.table_lineage` (primary) → workspace-path conventions (fallback). If neither resolves, mark the object `out_of_scope` in the schema card with `reason: no Spark-write producer in system.access.table_lineage`.
- **⛔ DAG ORDER**: Document upstream objects BEFORE downstream. Read `knowledge/skills/_kpi_views_index.json[].refs` and `system.access.table_lineage` to build the topological order. A downstream object whose upstream is in-scope but undocumented is BLOCKED — document the upstream first.
- **⛔ LINEAGE BEFORE DOCS**: Write `.lineage.md` BEFORE `.md`. Phase 5 READS the lineage file to assign tiers. Same contract as `dwh-semantic-doc/GATE-lineage-contract.mdc`.
- **⛔ THREE FILES PER OBJECT IN WIKI BUILD, WRITE ORDER IS SACRED**: Phase 5 produces exactly THREE files per object. Write them in THIS order:
  1. `{Object}.lineage.md` ← **LINEAGE** (column-level source mapping from Phase 4). Written FIRST because the wiki reads it.
  2. `{Object}.md` ← **THE WIKI** (6-section template). This is the primary artifact.
  3. `{Object}.review-needed.md` ← **SIDECAR** (UNVERIFIED items, questions, reviewer corrections). NEVER the wiki.
  **ALTER scripts (`.alter.sql`) are generated SEPARATELY** by Phase 6 (`tools/uc_pipelines/build_deploy_index.py` first, then `tools/deploy_alter_batch.py`). Do NOT generate `.alter.sql` during wiki build.
- **⛔ TIER SUFFIX ON EVERY DESCRIPTION**: Every column description in Section 3 (Elements) MUST end with `(Tier N — uc_object_or_notebook)`. This suffix is written verbatim to Unity Catalog by `tools/deploy_alter_batch.py`. Same rule, byte-identical format, as `dwh-semantic-doc` rule 19 — so the deploy tooling reuses verbatim.
- **⛔ TIER TRANSITIVITY**: Passthroughs inherit the **origin tier tag** from the upstream wiki — they do NOT introduce a new `(Tier 1 — {upstream_uc_object})` tag if the upstream column already says `(Tier 1 — Trade.PositionTbl)`. See §"Tier transitivity" in `GATE-lineage-contract.mdc`. UC view aliases are RELAYS, not origins.
- **⛔ SHARED COLUMN = SAME DESCRIPTION**: When this view passes through `HistoryID` from `Fact_CustomerAction`, the description here MUST equal the description in `knowledge/synapse/Wiki/DWH_dbo/Tables/Fact_CustomerAction.md`. Do NOT paraphrase. Do NOT rewrite. Do NOT change the tier.
- **⛔ UTF-8 FILE ENCODING ON ALL WRITES**: Every file write (`.md`, `.review-needed.md`, `.lineage.md`, `.alter.sql`) MUST use explicit `encoding="utf-8"`. Python: `open(path, "w", encoding="utf-8")`.
- **⛔ GOLDEN REFERENCE**: Read `GOLDEN-REFERENCE.mdc` once per session. Your output must match the **8-section** skeleton (§1 Business Meaning, §2 Business Logic, §3 Query Advisory, §4 Elements, §5 Lineage, §6 Relationships, §7 Sample Queries, §8 Atlassian). Earlier 6-section format is deprecated as of the Phase-6+9-port — the synthesis sections (§1/§2/§3) anchor on `concepts.json` and `formulas.json` produced by Phases 4.5/4.6.

## Out of scope (this pack)

- Genie / Tableau / Confluence Tier-1 mining — pure-UC eToro objects rarely have analyst-authored Confluence pages. Add later as optional Phase 3b if a target schema needs it.
- External Lineage API injection — UC auto-captures lineage for pure-UC Spark writes; no injection needed.
- DLT / Lakeflow pipeline semantics — the writer detection step records pipeline IDs, but the pack does not model pipeline-graph structure.
- Adversarial evaluator — defer until v1 stabilises with ≥5 wikis per schema.
